A 3 level map based around an old station for a petroleum company. The 3 levels comprise of sewers, the ground level (mostly outside, plus a corridor and storage room), and an office on the first floor. Has a rainy enviroment with some distant fog, part hillside part city location.

Lots of routes and a lot more complicated/fun than iceworld/poolparty. Took about 3-4 weeks to make.

Give it a go on your servers, it's sure to be a good'un.

I've optimised it, average FPS was 60+ (lowest 40-50fps).

fy_starfire
Starfire is set on a spinning space station that features jump platforms, a rotating satellite, slightly reduced gravity and random weapons. At the beginning of each round, every player receives either an AUG, SG552 or a Scout + a random pistol except USP and Deagle. They can then try to use jumppads, the central flank beneath the satellite or one of the side flanks to get to the enemy base. Taking the southern flank provides you with no cover by the central satellite while the southern route does provide you with cover but also makes you easily visible because of the bright spinning circles around the map. There are AWPs next to each spawn that you can only pick up with haphazardous strafe jumps that leave you extremely vulnerable to enemy fire. Textures are by Philip K. For the 3D Sky, I used some NASA pictures. More projects at acidmaps.net. If you are running this map on your server, please tell me so I can join and gather feedback regarding gameplay and possibly bugs.

I made this map for the new spiderman movie
I made the buildings, and textures and everything else, but MikeysJr. did the lighting

Here is my try for the main hall of the Spencer Mansion. I tried to make it as original and as good looking as possible, but since the source engine has its limitations, I could not add reflections, lightning effects nor some of the geometry without it completely soaking up the FPS. 

Since the map is quite small, I thought that the fight yard type would suit this map perfectly. Each player start off with a knife within close proximity of the enemy in different parts of the hall. Weapons can be found on key objects, drawers, chairs etc. just like in the game.
Map is in a RAR file, you know what to do!
